  <body>
    <div style="basic">
        <p begin="00:00:00.000" end="00:00:02.920" tts:direction="ltr">Hi, D 2,100 students.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:02.920" end="00:00:05.840" tts:direction="ltr">In this video, we are going to talk about
<br />data visualization.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:05.840" end="00:00:08.680" tts:direction="ltr">Now, this is something that I absolutely
<br />love.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:08.680" end="00:00:11.880" tts:direction="ltr">As we're wrapping up our data analysis
<br />module,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:11.880" end="00:00:15.200" tts:direction="ltr">I wanted to take some time and talk
<br />briefly about data visualization.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:15.200" end="00:00:18.440" tts:direction="ltr">I've created courses in data
<br />visualization,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:18.440" end="00:00:21.680" tts:direction="ltr">and so it's hard to condense it all down
<br />into a short video.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:21.680" end="00:00:24.720" tts:direction="ltr">But I wanted to give you just a short
<br />video recap</p>
        <p begin="00:00:24.720" end="00:00:27.440" tts:direction="ltr">of what is data viz and why does it
<br />matter?</p>
        <p begin="00:00:27.440" end="00:00:30.400" tts:direction="ltr">I'm going to give you a couple of examples
<br />here.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:30.400" end="00:00:33.320" tts:direction="ltr">What do you think when you see this?</p>
        <p begin="00:00:33.320" end="00:00:40.180" tts:direction="ltr">What do you think? You may say it's an
<br />alert, it's a call to action.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:40.180" end="00:00:42.900" tts:direction="ltr">You're immediately thinking, where's my
<br />charger?</p>
        <p begin="00:00:42.900" end="00:00:46.860" tts:direction="ltr">Or why didn't I turn on my low power mode
<br />earlier,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:46.860" end="00:00:50.500" tts:direction="ltr">or did I forget to charge my phone last
<br />night or have I've been</p>
        <p begin="00:00:50.500" end="00:00:51.900" tts:direction="ltr">spending too much time on my phone</p>
        <p begin="00:00:51.900" end="00:00:54.860" tts:direction="ltr">today because I actually did charge it
<br />last night.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:54.860" end="00:00:57.020" tts:direction="ltr">It's maybe a reflection point,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:57.020" end="00:00:59.980" tts:direction="ltr">it's a call to action of where's my
<br />charger and it's</p>
        <p begin="00:00:59.980" end="00:01:03.150" tts:direction="ltr">all through a very simple data
<br />visualization.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:03.150" end="00:01:06.520" tts:direction="ltr">So in this example, we are visualizing
<br />this data,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:06.520" end="00:01:09.480" tts:direction="ltr">this small amount of battery that is left.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:09.480" end="00:01:12.520" tts:direction="ltr">We are symbolizing here with this red
<br />line.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:12.520" end="00:01:17.360" tts:direction="ltr">We're using the battery icon as a
<br />reference point.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:17.360" end="00:01:20.720" tts:direction="ltr">We are very familiar with what a battery
<br />icon looks like.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:20.720" end="00:01:25.400" tts:direction="ltr">We're saying, Hey, there is just a little
<br />bit of battery left.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:25.400" end="00:01:27.680" tts:direction="ltr">Go and seek your charger.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:27.680" end="00:01:30.640" tts:direction="ltr">The color red can oftentimes mean stop,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:30.640" end="00:01:35.160" tts:direction="ltr">like a stop sign or a yield or something
<br />like that.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:35.160" end="00:01:38.840" tts:direction="ltr">It's calling our attention and making us
<br />aware.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:38.840" end="00:01:40.965" tts:direction="ltr">Now, what do you think of when you see
<br />this?</p>
        <p begin="00:01:40.965" end="00:01:45.050" tts:direction="ltr">Kind of same thing is here's a Google Map
<br />visualization,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:45.050" end="00:01:49.410" tts:direction="ltr">and if you're driving along here and you
<br />see,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:49.410" end="00:01:52.090" tts:direction="ltr">this is going to be bad here quick,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:52.090" end="00:01:56.490" tts:direction="ltr">you might hop off and grab some dinner and
<br />then continue on down.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:56.490" end="00:02:01.650" tts:direction="ltr">It can be data visualizations communicate
<br />data really clearly,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:01.650" end="00:02:05.130" tts:direction="ltr">hopefully, and are a call to action and
<br />help</p>
        <p begin="00:02:05.130" end="00:02:08.850" tts:direction="ltr">you synthesize the data and do something
<br />about it.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:08.850" end="00:02:12.440" tts:direction="ltr">All right. So why data visualization?</p>
        <p begin="00:02:12.440" end="00:02:17.280" tts:direction="ltr">First off, data visualization</p>
        <p begin="00:02:17.280" end="00:02:22.720" tts:direction="ltr">encompasses all visual representations
<br />that support the exploration,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:22.720" end="00:02:25.920" tts:direction="ltr">examination, communication of data.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:25.920" end="00:02:29.600" tts:direction="ltr">Data visualization helps to order
<br />information and to</p>
        <p begin="00:02:29.600" end="00:02:33.280" tts:direction="ltr">improve comprehension, interpretation, and
<br />memory.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:33.280" end="00:02:37.160" tts:direction="ltr">Basically, this is what it does is it
<br />amplifies cognition.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:37.160" end="00:02:38.995" tts:direction="ltr">They help us think.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:38.995" end="00:02:45.190" tts:direction="ltr">Okay. So just like this visualization back
<br />here, this amplifies cognition.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:45.190" end="00:02:48.510" tts:direction="ltr">It immediately triggers our brain as a
<br />call to action,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:48.510" end="00:02:51.190" tts:direction="ltr">maybe a reflection, something like that.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:51.190" end="00:02:54.590" tts:direction="ltr">So it is any sort of visualization,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:54.590" end="00:02:56.270" tts:direction="ltr">that supports the exploration,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:56.270" end="00:02:59.015" tts:direction="ltr">examination, and communication of data.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:59.015" end="00:03:02.040" tts:direction="ltr">So data visualization is definitely in
<br />demand.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:02.040" end="00:03:05.720" tts:direction="ltr">Here is the North America data
<br />visualization market size</p>
        <p begin="00:03:05.720" end="00:03:07.600" tts:direction="ltr">over the next few years,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:07.600" end="00:03:10.200" tts:direction="ltr">and we can see here we have that increase</p>
        <p begin="00:03:10.200" end="00:03:16.000" tts:direction="ltr">of that increase over time in billions of
<br />dollars.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:16.000" end="00:03:17.600" tts:direction="ltr">So we have seen this increase,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:17.600" end="00:03:20.920" tts:direction="ltr">and we are looking to continue to see this
<br />increase.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:20.920" end="00:03:25.120" tts:direction="ltr">So here when I think about my five senses,
<br />basically,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:25.120" end="00:03:26.960" tts:direction="ltr">this means there's jobs,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:26.960" end="00:03:30.120" tts:direction="ltr">there is demand for data visualization.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:30.120" end="00:03:32.720" tts:direction="ltr">I love job titles that are like</p>
        <p begin="00:03:32.720" end="00:03:35.480" tts:direction="ltr">data visualization analyst or things like
<br />that,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:35.480" end="00:03:38.600" tts:direction="ltr">and there's oftentimes a lot of job
<br />positions that just list</p>
        <p begin="00:03:38.600" end="00:03:47.025" tts:direction="ltr">data visualization as a preferred skill
<br />that somebody has.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:47.025" end="00:03:52.490" tts:direction="ltr">So when we think about our memories and we
<br />think about our five senses,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:52.490" end="00:03:56.650" tts:direction="ltr">there is one sense that dominates all
<br />others,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:56.650" end="00:03:59.210" tts:direction="ltr">and that is that is our sight.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:59.210" end="00:04:01.250" tts:direction="ltr">It dominates all of our senses.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:01.250" end="00:04:05.890" tts:direction="ltr">And so when we are communicating through
<br />these visualizations, it can,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:05.890" end="00:04:08.690" tts:direction="ltr">again, amplify cognition, allow us to</p>
        <p begin="00:04:08.690" end="00:04:12.275" tts:direction="ltr">think and help with our retention of the
<br />information as well.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:12.275" end="00:04:15.620" tts:direction="ltr">So when we are talking about data
<br />visualization,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:15.620" end="00:04:18.780" tts:direction="ltr">we use something called pre attentive
<br />attributes.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:18.780" end="00:04:21.420" tts:direction="ltr">Now, I know I'm throwing a lot at you in
<br />this one video,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:21.420" end="00:04:26.180" tts:direction="ltr">but I hope it to be really condensed and
<br />also just a lot of good information.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:26.180" end="00:04:29.220" tts:direction="ltr">So when we're looking at data
<br />visualizations,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:29.220" end="00:04:32.940" tts:direction="ltr">we use pre attentive attributes as we
<br />design them.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:32.940" end="00:04:35.860" tts:direction="ltr">Preattentive attributes are visual
<br />properties</p>
        <p begin="00:04:35.860" end="00:04:39.100" tts:direction="ltr">that we notice without using conscious
<br />effort to do so.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:39.100" end="00:04:41.020" tts:direction="ltr">When you are looking at the slide,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:41.020" end="00:04:45.070" tts:direction="ltr">which a which words stood out the most.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:45.070" end="00:04:49.270" tts:direction="ltr">You're thinking, Oh, these bright orange
<br />words did.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:49.270" end="00:04:52.310" tts:direction="ltr">You're right because I'm calling your
<br />attention there.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:52.310" end="00:04:57.030" tts:direction="ltr">I am using pre attentive attributes that
<br />call your attention to those words.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:57.030" end="00:05:02.240" tts:direction="ltr">I've bolded them. I've made them into a
<br />color that calls your attention.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:02.240" end="00:05:06.050" tts:direction="ltr">Same thing over here, if I'm looking at
<br />all of these purple dots,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:06.050" end="00:05:07.410" tts:direction="ltr">where does your eye go?</p>
        <p begin="00:05:07.410" end="00:05:09.610" tts:direction="ltr">It goes to the one that's different.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:09.610" end="00:05:12.170" tts:direction="ltr">The one that is a different color.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:12.170" end="00:05:14.690" tts:direction="ltr">We are pulling your eye there.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:14.930" end="00:05:18.050" tts:direction="ltr">This is not conscious effort,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:18.050" end="00:05:19.490" tts:direction="ltr">we are just saying, Hey,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:19.490" end="00:05:22.410" tts:direction="ltr">I want you to focus in on this one data
<br />point.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:22.410" end="00:05:26.170" tts:direction="ltr">This is a really good way to create data
<br />visualizations.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:26.170" end="00:05:28.850" tts:direction="ltr">Another thing to think about here is that</p>
        <p begin="00:05:28.850" end="00:05:31.810" tts:direction="ltr">we are using orange and we are using
<br />purple.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:31.810" end="00:05:33.970" tts:direction="ltr">These are complimentary colors.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:33.970" end="00:05:37.785" tts:direction="ltr">The provide a lot of contrast in the
<br />visualization.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:37.785" end="00:05:40.440" tts:direction="ltr">So I want to give you a quick challenge
